<p>I have some XML that looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;root&gt;   &lt;instructions type="array"&gt;     &lt;item type="string"&gt;Cannot do business directly with consumers&lt;/item&gt;     &lt;item type="string"&gt;Cannot marry a martian&lt;/item&gt;   &lt;/instructions&gt; &lt;/root&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and an <code>instructions</code> variable that looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>var instructions = myXDocument.XPathSelectElements("/root/instructions").Nodes(); </code></pre>  <p>I am attempting to concatenate all of the <code>item</code> strings, thusly:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>"Cannot do business directly with consumers, Cannot marry a martian"</p> </blockquote>  <p>and my attempt so far is</p>  <pre><code>instructions.Select(x =&gt; x.[[What do I put here?]]).Aggregate((i,j) =&gt; i + ", " + j) </code></pre>  <p>but having trouble figuring out how to get the inner text from each node in my lambda expression.  <code>x.ToString()</code> yields <code>"&lt;item type="string"&gt;Cannot do business directly with consumers&lt;/item&gt;"</code></p>